<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 30 at 6:50PM CDT until July 30 at 7:30PM CDT by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 730 PM CDT
FOR CENTRAL WEBSTER AND SOUTHWESTERN CLAIBORNE PARISHES...
At 649 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located just east of Cotton
Valley, or 12 miles north of Minden, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Minden, Cotton Valley, Evergreen, Holly Springs and Couchwood.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
